<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<methodology slug="puppeteer-stealth-proxy">
  <metadata>
    <tier>solo</tier>
    <group>dev</group>
    <domain>automation-tooling</domain>
    <summary>Evade bot detection in Puppeteer using puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth and manual navigator overrides; route traffic through single proxies or rotating proxy pools with per-browser authentication.</summary>
    <tags>
      <tag>puppeteer</tag>
      <tag>stealth</tag>
      <tag>proxy</tag>
      <tag>bot-detection</tag>
      <tag>browser-automation</tag>
    </tags>
    <difficulty>intermediate</difficulty>
    <created>2026-04-27</created>
    <languages>
      <language>javascript</language>
    </languages>
    <frameworks>
      <framework>puppeteer</framework>
    </frameworks>
    <related>
      <ref slug="puppeteer-launch-setup"/>
      <ref slug="puppeteer-session-management"/>
      <ref slug="puppeteer-agent-workflow"/>
    </related>
  </metadata>
  <content>
    <title>Puppeteer: Stealth Mode &amp; Proxy Support</title>

    <summary>Covers puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth for automated bot-detection evasion, manual navigator property overrides, single-proxy configuration, and rotating proxy pool patterns. Includes limitations and arms-race caveats for production scraping.</summary>

    <why>
      <p>Modern anti-bot systems (Cloudflare, Datadome, PerimeterX) fingerprint the browser through headless-mode tells: navigator.webdriver flag, missing plugin list, predictable languages array, Chrome DevTools socket exposure. The stealth plugin patches the most common tells automatically; manual overrides cover gaps. Proxy rotation prevents IP-based bans in high-volume scraping.</p>
    </why>

    <when-to-use>
      <list>
        <item>Scraping targets with basic bot-detection that checks navigator properties.</item>
        <item>Pipelines that must distribute requests across multiple IP addresses to avoid rate-limiting.</item>
        <item>Any flow that requires appearing as a regular browser to bypass simple fingerprinting.</item>
      </list>
    </when-to-use>

    <when-not-to-use>
      <list>
        <item>Long-running scraping farms against Cloudflare Enterprise or Datadome-defended targets — stealth plugin lags behind detection; switch to Playwright + playwright-extra/stealth or a managed service like Bright Data.</item>
        <item>Anything involving credentials, CAPTCHAs, or 2FA in a fully automated loop — human-in-the-loop checkpoints are required (see puppeteer-agent-workflow).</item>
      </list>
    </when-not-to-use>

    <section name="stealth-plugin">
      <example type="good" title="puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth setup">
        <code lang="javascript"><![CDATA[const puppeteer = require('puppeteer-extra');
const StealthPlugin = require('puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth');

puppeteer.use(StealthPlugin());

const browser = await puppeteer.launch({ headless: true });]]></code>
        <note>puppeteer-extra wraps the standard puppeteer API; all existing code works unchanged after the use() call.</note>
      </example>
      <rule>
        <statement>Pick one evasion stance — either puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth alone or manual overrides alone — and document it. Mixing both can create contradictory navigator props that the agent then asserts on incorrectly.</statement>
        <rationale>Stealth plugin can change navigator props the agent later asserts on; a single documented stance prevents brittle assertions in subsequent page.evaluate() calls.</rationale>
      </rule>
    </section>

    <section name="manual-evasion">
      <p>Manual navigator overrides for environments where puppeteer-extra is unavailable:</p>
      <example type="good" title="Override webdriver, plugins, and languages">
        <code lang="javascript"><![CDATA[// Override webdriver property
await page.evaluateOnNewDocument(() => {
  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'webdriver', {
    get: () => undefined
  });
});

// Override plugins (empty list is a headless tell)
await page.evaluateOnNewDocument(() => {
  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'plugins', {
    get: () => [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
  });
});

// Override languages
await page.evaluateOnNewDocument(() => {
  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'languages', {
    get: () => ['en-US', 'en']
  });
});]]></code>
        <note>evaluateOnNewDocument runs before any page script — overrides are in place from the first JS execution cycle.</note>
      </example>
    </section>

    <section name="proxy-support">
      <example type="good" title="Single proxy with authentication">
        <code lang="javascript"><![CDATA[const browser = await puppeteer.launch({
  args: ['--proxy-server=http://proxy.example.com:8080']
});

// With per-page proxy authentication
const page = await browser.newPage();
await page.authenticate({
  username: 'proxyuser',
  password: 'proxypass'
});]]></code>
      </example>
      <example type="good" title="Rotating proxy pool">
        <code lang="javascript"><![CDATA[const proxies = [
  'http://proxy1.example.com:8080',
  'http://proxy2.example.com:8080',
  'http://proxy3.example.com:8080'
];

let proxyIndex = 0;

async function getNextProxy() {
  const proxy = proxies[proxyIndex];
  proxyIndex = (proxyIndex + 1) % proxies.length;
  return proxy;
}

async function createBrowserWithProxy() {
  const proxy = await getNextProxy();
  return puppeteer.launch({
    args: [`--proxy-server=${proxy}`]
  });
}]]></code>
        <note>Each browser instance is bound to one proxy at launch time; to switch proxy, close the browser and launch a new one.</note>
      </example>
    </section>

    <antipattern>
      <description>Running unbounded retries on 429 responses from managed browser services (Browserless, ScrapingBee) without a circuit breaker.</description>
      <reason>Unbounded retries on rate-limit responses burn budget fast. Set --max-retries=2 and circuit-break on 4xx; surface the error to the caller instead of looping silently.</reason>
    </antipattern>

    <see-also>
      <link href="https://github.com/berstend/puppeteer-extra"/>
      <link href="https://github.com/Sparticuz/chromium"/>
      <ref slug="puppeteer-launch-setup"/>
      <ref slug="puppeteer-agent-workflow"/>
    </see-also>
  </content>
</methodology>
